question:We buy one kilo of tomatoes which costs one euro and twenty cents; and we pay with a five euro bill. How much change do we get back?  
answers:four euros and seventy cents,three euros and eighty cents,two euros and eighty cents,eighty cents
correctAnswer:three euros and eighty cents

question:We buy a box of sweets which costs eight euro and ninety cents; and we pay with a ten euro bill. How much change do we get back? 
answers:one euro and fifteen cents,two euros and ten cents,one euro and ten cents,forty cents
correctAnswer:one euro and ten cents
